turns.contribution:
Thank you, Madam Chair.
              On Monday, April 20, we passed some motions. One of them read as follows:e) the government ensure that the Canada Emergency Response Benefit and the Canada Emergency Student Benefit  are offered in a manner that meets their objective while encouraging employment in all circumstances;
              A student who works 18 hours a week at minimum wage will make the same income as one who works 43 hours a week, also at minimum wage. Which option do you think students will choose?
